cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about a convolutional neural network architecture for modeling statistical regularities in natural images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed architecture, which suggests that it could be relevant to the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on image processing tasks, which could also make it relevant to the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
